{"questionId":"27208","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A student investigating the relationship between chemical reactions and temperature finds&nbsp;the Arrhenius equation on the internet.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>A</mi><msup><mtext>e</mtext><mrow><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mi>T</mi></mfrac></mrow></msup></math></p>\n<p>This equation links a variable <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> with the temperature <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>c</mi></math> are positive&nbsp;constants and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Arrhenius equation predicts that the graph of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math> against <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math> is a straight line.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The following data are found for a particular reaction, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>T</mi></math> is measured in Kelvin&nbsp;and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>k</mi></math> is measured in <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mtext>cm</mtext><mn>3</mn></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>mol</mtext><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup><mo> </mo><msup><mtext>s</mtext><mrow><mo>−</mo><mn>1</mn></mrow></msup></math>:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/aa3d3ff490da821e38c0fa0bed446caa6a20a8b6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find the equation of the regression line for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math> on <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>an attempt to convert data to&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac></math>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>e.g. at least one correct row in the following table</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/4b562b791e9e6795ecfbf0366e5643a9c17bf091.png\"></p>\n<p>line is&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>ln</mi><mo> </mo><mi>k</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>13400</mn><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>13383</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>×</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mi>T</mi></mfrac><mo>+</mo><mn>15</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>0107</mn><mo>…</mo></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"27208","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.4d","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find the equation of the regression line for ln k on 1T.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","SL 2.1—Equations of straight lines, parallel and perpendicular","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.10—Scaling large numbers, log-log graphs","Topic 1—Number and algebra","AHL 1.9—Log laws"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}